&lt;li data-start=&quot;1691&quot; data-end=&quot;1824&quot;&gt;Deep interest and practical experience with&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;1870&quot; data-end=&quot;1887&quot;&gt;Generative AI&lt;/strong&gt;, including LLMs, RAG, vector search, embeddings, agents, and AI workflow orchestration.&

&lt;h1&gt;AI Platform &amp;amp; Integration Engineer&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an &lt;strong&gt;AI Platform &amp;amp; Integration Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; with at least &lt;strong&gt;4 years of professional experience&lt;/strong&gt; to help design, build, and maintain cloud-based integrations, automation workflows, AI-enabled platforms, and infrastructure as code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of &lt;strong&gt;DevOps&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;platform engineering, cloud infrastructure, AI systems, and developer workflow automation&lt;/strong&gt;. The ideal candidate is comfortable working across tools such as &lt;strong&gt;Jira, Bitbucket, AWS, SageMaker, Redshift and AWS Bedrock&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and enjoys connecting systems together to automate business and engineering processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for integrating platforms, configuring AI services and agents, building reusable infrastructure components, and supporting internal teams with scalable, secure, and maintainable cloud solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and build integrations between internal and external systems such as &lt;strong&gt;Jira, Bitbucket, AWS services&lt;/strong&gt; using APIs and webhooks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop automation workflows that connect project management tools, repositories, cloud services, and AI platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and manage AWS services, including &lt;strong&gt;Amazon SageMaker, Amazon Redshift, Amazon Bedrock&lt;/strong&gt;, and related cloud infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set up and configure &lt;strong&gt;AI agents&lt;/strong&gt; and agent-based workflows using AWS Bedrock as LLM provider.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write, maintain, and improve &lt;strong&gt;infrastructure as code&lt;/strong&gt; using &lt;strong&gt;Pulumi and/or Terraform&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support CI/CD workflows and repository automation in &lt;strong&gt;Bitbucket&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Jira automation, webhooks, APIs, and event-driven workflows to streamline engineering and operational processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with data, engineering, AI, and platform teams to understand requirements and deliver reliable technical solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document integrations, infrastructure components, runbooks, and operational procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot issues across cloud infrastructure, integrations, AI services, and automated workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least &lt;strong&gt;4 years of professional experience&lt;/strong&gt; in cloud engineering, platform engineering, DevOps, infrastructure, integrations, or a similar technical role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with &lt;strong&gt;AWS cloud services&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with &lt;strong&gt;infrastructure as code&lt;/strong&gt;, preferably using &lt;strong&gt;Terraform and/or Pulumi&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with APIs, webhooks, event-driven workflows, and system integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with source control platforms such as &lt;strong&gt;Bitbucket&lt;/strong&gt;, Git workflows, pull requests, and repository automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of CI/CD concepts and modern software delivery practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong troubleshooting, debugging, and documentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work cross-functionally with engineering, data, product, and business stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
